HEADWORD: Daughterly
<hw>Daugh"ter*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Becoming a daughter;
filial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sir Thomas liked her natural and dear <qex>daughterly</qex>
affection towards him.</q> <rj><qau>Cavendish.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
